5/ ... And once you're famous virtually, you can keep putting out hits for a long, long time. Thanks to Genies, we may be able to get the band back together and release some music in The Metaverse. We have six completed songs yet to release! ...

4/ But with the design appeal and the consumer recognition of Genies avatars and the vast accessories of The Warehouse coupled with the new business model opportunities of NFTs and The Metaverse, it is possible that many enterprising music acts could make it to the big time. ...

3/ ... At a cost of roughly $1,000 per original outfit and $200 per TikTok video, pursuing fame on social media proved to be slow going and financially risky for a new music group. Breaking into the music industry is hard enough without all of the 3D costs. ...

2/ ...and after the photogrammetry, the retopologizing, the rigging, the hairstyles, etc., we spent about $25,000 per character, and in the end we got expert and consumer feedback that are characters weren't very appealing. ...

1/ Back in 2019, we were a music team trying to create a virtual music artist business using a traditional 3D pipeline and Web2-style social media. "How hard can it be, we thought?" Let's just say we spent a lot of money for that education. We decided to pursue realism...
